title: The DLR Thermofluid Stream Library
abstract: The DLR Thermofluid Stream Library is a free open-source library for the robust modeling of complex thermofluid architectures. Designed to be easy to use and easy to adapt and enriched by a number of examples, this library can be used as basis for many different applications such as thermal management of electric cars, power plants, or building physics.
